  <h2>Analysis Conclusion</h2>
    <p>The two contenders for the solar garden power supply were lead – acid batteries, and lithium ion batteries. Hands down lithium ion batteries are the better option for this project in terms of utility. They have a higher power density and have a larger amount of discharge cycles than lead acid batteries. Unfortunately, they cost a lot of money. Lead – acid batteries work for this project because we are not concerned about power density since we do not need to move the power supply around. Also, while discharge cycles are extremely important for this project, lead – acid batteries have a minimum of approximately 500 discharge cycle. Enough to last at least one season of growing, and most of the second. Since both lithium ion batteries and lead – acid batteries are very recyclable this is not a consideration.</p>
